{{Quote|Regarding the fans, I am truly humbled and it touches my heart that someone would care about Mace Towani or Eric Walker. I really enjoy listening to all the personal stories from my fans. It really touches my heart to know that maybe I helped them escape this world, if only for a brief amount of time while they were engaged in watching Mace and Cindel try to save their parents. Many of them have shared with me how they would pretend they were Mace while they were playing with friends or other relatives and if I was able to help them by being a mentor or someone they wished they were like. I am thankful to have participated as a positive role model in their lives.|Eric Walker in an interview with Wattographs.com|<ref name="Wattographs">{{WebCite|url=http://www.wattographs.com/articles/recollections/recollections-ericwalker.html|text=Eric Walker: Mace Towani|author=Dennis Pellegrom & Gary Price|nolive=1|archivedate=20061121184026}}</ref>}}
'''Eric Walker''' (born [[January 31]], [[1970]])<ref name="This Week! Ep1" /> is a former child actor who played [[Mace Towani]] in ''[[Caravan of Courage: An Ewok Adventure]]'' ([[1984]])<ref name="Caravan of Courage" /> and ''[[Ewoks: The Battle for Endor]]'' ([[1985]]).<ref name="Battle for Endor">''[[Ewoks: The Battle for Endor]]''</ref> He has since become a writer and [[Wikipedia:Electronic music|electronic musician]]; his first album contains the song "Return to Endor", inspired by the Ewok films.<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://www.fanthatracks.com/interviews/catching-eric-walker-mace-towani-caravan-of-courage-battle-endor|text=Catching up with Eric Walker: Mace Towani from Caravan of Courage and Battle for Endor|author=O'Brien, Adam|date=2018-02-16|archivedate=20200904173922}}</ref>

